                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front with an embedded low pressure system lies west of Kangaroo Island. The low is expected to move north and over the Eyre Peninsula today, weakening as it moves into NSW on Tuesday. A weak ridge of high pressure begins to move across SA later in the week.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
